                \b In April 1782, the North ministry was replaced by a new British government which accepted American independence and 
                \b began negotiating the Treaty of Paris, ratified on September 3, 1783. 
                \b The war officially ended on September 3, 1783 when Britain accepted American independence in the Treaty of Paris, 
                \b while the Treaties of Versailles resolved separate conflicts with France and Spain.    

